
[1]intermit

   INTERMIT', v.t. [L. intermitto; inter and mitto, to send.]

   To cause to cease for a time; to interrupt; to suspend.

   Pray to the gods, to intermit the plague

   That needs must light on this ingratitude.

      INTERMIT', v.i. To cease for a time; to go off at intervals; as a
    fever. A tertian fever intermits every other day. The pulse sometimes
                       intermits for a second of time.
